				<wikidot:authorName>CMDR_AIDAN</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2946284</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I really like this, an interesting, simple idea that keeps you reading. But, maybe this makes me a jerk, I'm seeing the phrase &quot;no trace was found&quot; a lot. Is &quot;went missing&quot; or &quot;could not be found/located&quot; better? I know that &quot;no trace&quot; makes sense but it seems a little too unprofessional (what's the word?) to me. I don't know. Still, fantastic job!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
